Notable changes to the Apache-2.0-licensed portions since 2026 (Copyright
(c) 2026 Immanuel Friedrichsen, licensed under the same Apache License 2.0,
as required by Section 4(b)):

- **Toolchain modernization**: replaced JCenter (repository shut down in
  2021/22), Android Gradle Plugin 3.1.4 â†’ 8.5.2, ndk-build â†’ CMake,
  AndroidX migration.
- **`resize()` real implementation** (`AbstractUVCCameraHandler`): the
  original method was a permanent `UnsupportedOperationException` stub â€”
  never implemented. All previewâ†”capture mode switching silently no-oped
  through this before the fix. Real implementation added: stop preview â†’
  `setPreviewSize()` â†’ resume preview on the same surface. Later found
  in-place `resize()` is unreliable in BOTH directions on this hardware
  (never delivers a complete frame above 640x480 going up, `Application
  transferred too few scanlines` on every frame coming back down) â€” the
  app layer now always does a full `close()`+`open()` cycle with the
  retained `UsbControlBlock` instead (`reopenAtSize()` in
  `bookscanner-app`), not the driver's `resize()`.
- **Native data race fixed** in `CallbackPipeline::do_capture()`: the
  frame-delivery thread read shared Java callback references without a
  mutex while `setFrameCallback()` mutated them under lock elsewhere â€”
  caused a `jmethodID was NULL` native crash after several mode-switch
  cycles.
- **Unconditional `DetachCurrentThread()` fixed** in
  `UVCButtonCallback.cpp`/`UVCStatusCallback.cpp`: detached JNI threads
  that were already attached, causing an `attempting to detach while
  still running code` native crash on repeated camera reopen cycles
  (relevant once the app started doing real close+reopen cycles for
  every capture and mode switch).
- **Android 12+/13+/14+ USB/permission compatibility fixes**:
  `PendingIntent` now requires explicit `FLAG_IMMUTABLE`/`FLAG_MUTABLE`
  (Android 12+); `FLAG_MUTABLE` is forbidden on implicit intents (Android
  14+) â€” permission intent is now scoped to the app's own package via
  `setPackage()`; `registerReceiver()` requires explicit
  `RECEIVER_EXPORTED`/`RECEIVER_NOT_EXPORTED` (Android 13+);
  `getSerialNumber()`/`getManufacturerName()` throw `SecurityException`
  if called before permission is granted (Android 12+) â€” now called only
  after permission is confirmed.
- **USB permission request queuing, two rounds of fixes**: (1) when two
  UVC devices attach at once (dual-camera cold start), two simultaneous
  `USBMonitor.requestPermission()` calls collide at the OS level â€” the
  second `UsbPermissionActivity` launch is immediately cancelled
  (`result code=3`) instead of shown, leaving the second camera silently
  unconnected. Fixed with a strict in-app queue: only one
  `requestPermission()` in flight at a time, the next is fired only after
  `onConnect()`/`onCancel()` resolves the previous one. (2) Root-cause
  follow-up found that the vendored `USBMonitor.mDeviceCheckRunnable`
  (background poller, `USBMonitor.java`) re-fires `onAttach()` for **all**
  currently attached devices whenever *any* device's permission count
  changes â€” not just the newly attached one. Without a guard this could
  re-enqueue an already-handled device into the sequential queue,
  reopening the original collision. Fixed at the app layer by tracking
  already-handled device paths (`handledDeviceNames`, keyed by the stable
  USB bus device name) and ignoring repeat `onAttach()` calls for a
  device until it is actually detached.
- **Orphaned preview stream root-caused**: `onSurfaceDestroy()` did
  nothing besides logging â€” switching the active camera slot (e.g. LEFT â†’
  RIGHT) left the native preview thread of the deselected camera running
  indefinitely against an already-destroyed `Surface` (`BufferQueue has
  been abandoned` every ~0.5s, no upper bound observed). A device left in
  this state this way was found to stay in a broken
  `Application transferred too few scanlines` state even across a full
  app process restart â€” only a physical USB replug recovered it (no
  public, root-free Android API exists to force a USB port reset). Fixed
  by calling `stopPreview()` for the deselected camera on
  `onSurfaceDestroy()`.
- Extended UVC control APIs (exposed to the app layer): focus, white
  balance, brightness, contrast, sharpness, gain, gamma, saturation, hue,
  zoom â€” auto and manual, plus dynamic supported-resolution querying.

